<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="chocolate-sheet" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Chocolate Sheet Cake (Aunt Evelyn) </title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell><term>Cake:</term></cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup oil</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>4 tablespoons cocoa (30 gm)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup water</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 cups flour (250 gm)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 cups sugar (400 gm)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 eggs, beaten</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon cinnamon (optional)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon baking soda</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup buttermilk or clabbered milk</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><term>Frosting:</term></cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>6 tablespoons milk</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>4 tablespoons cocoa (30 gm)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>3 \frac{1}{2}</m> to 4 cups powdered sugar (480 gm)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup nuts (optional)</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          For the cake, bring butter, oil, cocoa, and water to a boil.  Pour over the sugar and flour, and blend well.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Add the eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda, and milk.  Blend well.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Place in a greased 9" x 13" pan.  Bake at <m>400^\circ</m> for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out dry.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          For the frosting, melt the butter and mix in the milk and cocoa well.  Bring to a rapid boil and remove from heat.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Stir in powdered sugar until smooth. Add vanilla and nuts.  Spread on cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>